Classes

class  GisXmlSkipElementHandler
 GisXmlSkipHandler can be used to skip an XML element, when reading an XML document via GisXmlReader. It is a GisXmlSaxHandler with no callback implementations. Therefore, if another GisXmlSaxHandler's XmlStartElement callback returns a GisXmlSkipElementHandler then there are no more SAX events until the end of the current element is reached. More...
